<recipe>
<title>
California Club Croissant Sandwich
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 10 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: croissant, lunch, sandwich
SERVINGS: 2
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="2.0">Cheddar</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 oz ">Chicken</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 oz ">Meat</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 oz ">Meat</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0">Cheese</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5">Tomato</ingredient><ingredient amount="0.5">Avocado</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Slice each croissant horizontally.
Layer one slice Sargento&#174; Sharp Cheddar Sliced Cheese on each croissant.
Top with layers of chicken, ham, and turkey.
Add one slice Sargento&#174; Baby Swiss Sliced Cheese over meat.
Top with each sandwich with bacon, 1/4 tomato slices, 1/4 avocado slices, and a piece of lettuce.
Spread top of croissant with mayo and mustard.
Place top piece croissant over lettuce.
Cut diagonally to serve.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>